{
  "texts": [
    "We infer that Polη interferes with Polκ PCNA-binding and reduces tolerance of TMZ-induced lesions.",
    "To comprehensively define the genome maintenance network (including RAD18-interacting pathways) that mediates tolerance of TMZ-induced DNA damage, we performed a CRISPR-based loss-offunction screen.",
    "We transduced RAD18 +/+ and RAD18 -/-U373 cells with a sgRNA library targeting 504 DDR genes spanning every major DNA repair pathway (Supplementary Data 1).",
    "Stably-infected cells were grown for 20 population doublings (PD) in the presence or absence of TMZ.",
    "Finally, we sequenced lentivirus integrated cassette DNA to quantify abundance of each sgRNA sequence relative to all mapped reads for each experimental group (Fig. 5a, Supplementary Data 2)."
  ]
}